Osc1Type: What type of oscillator to use for oscillator 1
Osc1Cents: The cents (hundreds of a semitone) of oscillator 1. [-100.0, 100.0]
Osc1PulseWidth: The pulsewidth of oscillator 1 (when using a square wave type oscillator). [0.0, 1.0]
Osc2Type: What type of oscillator to use for oscillator 2
Osc2Cents: The cents (hundreds of a semitone) of oscillator 2. [-100.0, 100.0]
Osc2PulseWidth: The pulsewidth of oscillator 2 (when using a square wave type oscillator). [0.0, 1.0]
Portamento: The amount of portamento to use, which is the amount of pitch sliding from current note to next [0.0, 1.0]
Spread: The amount of stereo spread to use between oscillator 1 and oscillator 2 [0.0, 1.0]
Pan: The stereo pan to use. 0.0 is center. -1.0 is left, 1.0 is right.
LFO1Frequency: The frequency to use for LFO 1 (in hz) [0.0, 50.0]
LFO1Gain: The linear gain to use for LFO 1 [0.0, 1.0]
LFO1Type: The type of LFO to use for LFO 1
LFO1Mode: The mode to use for LFO 1
LFO1PatchType: The built-in patch type to use for LFO 1 (you can route this to any patchable parameter using the Patches parameter)
LFO2Frequency: The frequency to use for LFO 2 (in hz) [0.0, 50.0]
LFO2Gain: The linear gain to use for LFO 2 [0.0, 1.0]
LFO2Type: The type of LFO to use for LFO 2
LFO2Mode: The mode to use for LFO 2
LFO2PatchType: The built-in patch type to use for LFO 2 (you can route this to any patchable parameter using the Patches parameter)
GainDb: The overall gain to use for the synthesizer in dB [-90.0, 20.0]
AttackTime: The amplitude envelope attack time (in ms) [0.0, 10000]
DecayTime: The amplitude envelope decay time (in ms)[0.0, 10000]
SustainGain: The amplitude envelope sustain amount (linear gain) [0.0, 1.0]
ReleaseTime: The amplitude envelope release time (in ms) [0.0, 10000]
ModEnvPatchType: The built-in patch type for the envelope modulator
ModEnvBiasPatchType: The built-in patch type for the envelope modulator bias output. Bias is when the envelope output is offset by the sustain gain.
ModulationEnvelopeDepth: The "depth" (i.e. how much) modulation envelope to use. This scales the modulation envelope output. [0.0, 1.0]
ModulationEnvelopeAttackTime: The modulation envelope attack time (in ms) [0.0, 10000]
ModulationEnvelopeDecayTime: The modulation envelope decay time (in ms) [0.0, 10000]
ModulationEnvelopeSustainGain: The modulation envelope sustain gain (linear gain) [0.0, 1.0]
ModulationEnvelopeReleaseTime: The modulation envelope release time (in ms) [0.0, 10000]
FilterType: The output filter type (lowpass, highpass, bandpass, bandstop)
FilterAlgorithm: The output filter circuit/algorithm type (one-pole ladder, ladder, state-variable)
StereoDelayMode: The stereo delay mode of the synth
StereoDelayFeedback: The amount of feedback in the stereo delay line [0.0, 1.0]
StereoDelayWetlevel: The output wet level to use for the stereo delay time [0.0, 1.0]
StereoDelayRatio: The ratio between left and right stereo delay lines (wider value is more separation) [0.0, 1.0]
ChorusDepth: The depth of the chorus effect [0.0, 1.0]
ChorusFeedback: The amount of feedback in the chorus effect [0.0, 1.0]
Patches: The modular synth patch cords to use for the synth. Allows routing the LFO1/LFO2 and Modulation Envelope to any patchable destination.
bEnablePolyphony: Whether or not to allow multiple synth voices.
bEnableUnison: Enables forcing the oscillators to have no stereo spread.
bEnableOscillatorSync: Whether or not oscillator sync is enabled. Oscillator sync forces oscillator 2's phase to align with oscillator 1's phase.
bInvertModulationEnvelope: Whether or not to invert the modulation envelope
bInvertModulationEnvelopeBias: Whether or not to invert the modulation envelope bias output
bLegato: Whether or not to use legato mode.
bRetrigger: Whether or not to use retrigger mode.
bStereoDelayEnabled: Whether or not stereo delay is enabled on the synth
bChorusEnabled: Whether or not the chorus effect is enabled
